    "I focus here on the effects of deepfakes on knowledge in order to simplify the discussion and because, on the face of things, these effects might seem relatively easily addressed by algorithms for the automatic detection of deepfakes.",
    "The term 'deepfake' is sometimes used to refer to media items in generalincluding photos, audio, and video-that are generated using deep learning techniques.",
    "More commonly, the term is used to refer specifically to video footage that uses deep learning techniques to superimpose the likenesses of persons over existing recorded videos or live video streams.",
    "I focus on deepfakes, defined in this relatively narrow way, in what follows.",
    "While such deepfakes have to this point overwhelmingly taken the form of pornography (Cox, 2019), the potential of deepfakes to play a deceptive role was recognized early on and is increasingly being realized."
  ],
